ttyd for pfSense adds a Diagnostics menu entry that embeds a browser terminal.

The terminal backend is ttyd, and the shell session first prompts for a login
name, then runs ssh -tt to 127.0.0.1:22. This keeps the
interactive shell behind pfSense SSH authentication while still supporting
full TTY behavior such as editors, pagers, Ctrl-C, job control, and curses
programs.

The bundled ttyd runtime is installed privately under
/usr/local/pfSense-pkg-ttyd, and HTTPS uses the pfSense WebGUI certificate
instead of generating a separate ttyd certificate.
